  "time_ut": 1660937536,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0baf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't take the Anti-Terrorism Act into your own hands",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Amnesty International has emphasized that the government should stop using the Anti-Terrorism Act to stop the activities of the demonstrators fighting against the government and the government should take steps to repeal the Anti-Terrorism Act.",
        "Amnesty International has urged the Sri Lankan government not to use the draconian Anti-Terrorism Act to control demonstrations, saying that it is deeply concerned by reports that Vasantha Mudalike, the founder of the Tamtu University Students' Union, is currently being detained by the authorities in the Terrorism Investigation Unit.",
        "Amnesty International has pointed out that the government should move to repeal the Anti-Terrorism Act instead of implementing it, and that it is against international law to arbitrarily detain protesters and charge them with serious criminal offenses that are not justified by their actions, such as terrorism-related charges."
      ],
